newsitem.title: SOUTH KOREA: S.Korea's KFA seeks 52,500 tonnes of feed corn.
newsitem.headline: S.Korea's KFA seeks 52,500 tonnes of feed corn.

text.p: The Korea Feed Association (KFA) of South Korea invited on Tuesday tenders for 52,500 tonnes of feed corn, traders said.
Shipment was set on seller's option for July 7-26, 1997, if it is from the Pacific Northwest, for June 16-July 6 if from the U.S. Gulf or June 11-30 if from Argentina, traders said.
Arrival is scheduled for next August 5 at the southern port cities of Pusan and Ulsan, they said.
